  "referred_to_by": [
    {
      "type": "LinguisticObject",
      "content": "An oil sketch on prepared cardboard (29 x 41.3 cm) by **George Hendrik Breitner** (Rotterdam, 1857 – Amsterdam, 1923), depicting two young girls in the dunes, painted en plein air during his period living in **Loosduinen**, near The Hague (c. 1884–1886). Brown cardboard shows through the paint in places; preliminary chalk lines are still visible. Breitner told his friend Willem Witsen he intended to develop approximately twenty such studies into *\"een groot ding\"* — a grand large-scale work that was apparently never completed. Acquired in **1968** with support from the Olga Heldring Fonds, under the Fundatie Van den Santheuvel, Sobbe. Designated one of Teylers' **50 Topstukken**.",
